- "Last six months" refers to the six-month period preceding the current date.; 
- Performance metric values are assumed to be the most recent values recorded for each robot.; 
- The query focuses on robots that have undergone maintenance, implying that their performance metrics are of particular interest after maintenance activities.

sql:
SELECT robot_name
FROM robots
WHERE installation_date = (SELECT MAX(installation_date) FROM robots);

SELECT robot_name, manufacturer
FROM robots
ORDER BY robot_name ASC;

